3. –ì—Ä–∞–Ω—É–ª—è—Ä–Ω–∞—è –ø—Ä–∏–≤–∞—Ç–Ω–æ—Å—Ç—å: –ü–æ–ª–Ω–∞—è –ø—Ä–æ–∑—Ä–∞—á–Ω–æ—Å—Ç—å —á–∞—Å—Ç–æ –±—ã–≤–∞–µ—Ç –Ω–µ–≤—ã–≥–æ–¥–Ω–æ–π –≤ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Ç–µ–≥–∏—á–µ—Å–∫–∏—Ö –Ω–∞—Å—Ç—Ä–æ–π–∫–∞—Ö –∏ –º–æ–∂–µ—Ç –±—ã—Ç—å –∫–æ–Ω—Ç—Ä–ø—Ä–æ–¥—É–∫—Ç–∏–≤–Ω–æ–π –≤ —Å–æ—Ü–∏–∞–ª—å–Ω—ã—Ö –Ω–∞—Å—Ç—Ä–æ–π–∫–∞—Ö, –µ—Å–ª–∏ –æ–Ω–∞ —Å–Ω–∏–∂–∞–µ—Ç —Å—Ç–∏–º—É–ª—ã –∫ —É—á–∞—Å—Ç–∏—é. –ö—Ä–∏–ø—Ç–æ–≥—Ä–∞—Ñ–∏—è –º–æ–∂–µ—Ç –ø–æ–º–æ—á—å –æ–ø—Ä–µ–¥–µ–ª–∏—Ç—å –Ω–æ–≤—ã–µ —Å–æ—Å—Ç–∞–≤–Ω—ã–µ –ø—Ä–∏–º–∏—Ç–∏–≤—ã –¥–ª—è –ø—Ä–∏–≤–∞—Ç–Ω–æ—Å—Ç–∏, –ø–æ–∑–≤–æ–ª—è—é—â–∏–µ DAO –∏ —É—á–∞—Å—Ç–Ω–∏–∫–∞–º DAO —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Ç–µ–≥–∏—á–µ—Å–∫–∏ –¥–µ–π—Å—Ç–≤–æ–≤–∞—Ç—å, –¥–∞–∂–µ —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–∞—è –Ω–∞ –ø—É–±–ª–∏—á–Ω–æ–º —Ä–µ–µ—Å—Ç—Ä–µ. –û–¥–Ω–∞–∫–æ, —Å—É—â–µ—Å—Ç–≤—É—é—Ç —Å–ª—É—á–∞–∏, –∫–æ–≥–¥–∞ DAO —Ç—Ä–µ–±—É–µ—Ç—Å—è –Ω–µ–∫–æ—Ç–æ—Ä–∞—è —Ñ–æ—Ä–º–∞ –ø—Ä–∏–≤–∞—Ç–Ω–æ—Å—Ç–∏, –Ω–∞–ø—Ä–∏–º–µ—Ä, –∫–æ–≥–¥–∞ —Ä–∞–∑–º–µ—Ä –∫–∞–∑–Ω–∞—á–µ–π—Å—Ç–≤–∞ DAO —Å—Ç–∞–Ω–æ–≤–∏—Ç—Å—è –∏–∑–≤–µ—Å—Ç–µ–Ω –ø—É–±–ª–∏—á–Ω–æ, —á—Ç–æ –º–æ–∂–µ—Ç —Å—Ç–∞—Ç—å –∑–Ω–∞—á–∏—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω—ã–º –Ω–µ–¥–æ—Å—Ç–∞—Ç–∫–æ–º.

4. –£—è–∑–≤–∏–º–æ—Å—Ç–∏ DAO: –í–∫–ª—é—á–∞—è –≤–æ—Å–ø—Ä–∏–∏–º—á–∏–≤–æ—Å—Ç—å –∫ –ø–æ—Ç–µ—Ä–µ –∏–ª–∏ –Ω–µ–≤–Ω–∏–º–∞–Ω–∏—é –∫–ª—é—á–µ–≤—ã—Ö —É—á–∞—Å—Ç–Ω–∏–∫–æ–≤ –∏–ª–∏ –∞–¥–º–∏–Ω–∏—Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Ç–æ—Ä–æ–≤, —É—Å—Ç–æ–π—á–∏–≤–æ—Å—Ç—å –∫ –∞—Ç–∞–∫–∞–º 51%, —Å–∫–æ—Ä–æ—Å—Ç—å –∏ –æ—Ç–∑—ã–≤—á–∏–≤–æ—Å—Ç—å –Ω–∞ –∫—Ä–∏–∑–∏—Å—ã, —Å–ø–æ—Å–æ–±–Ω–æ—Å—Ç—å —É–ø—Ä–∞–≤–ª—è—Ç—å —Ä–∞–∑–Ω–æ–≥–ª–∞—Å–∏—è–º–∏, –≤–æ—Å–ø—Ä–∏–∏–º—á–∏–≤–æ—Å—Ç—å –∫ —Ñ–æ—Ä–∫–∏–Ω–≥—É, –∏ –≤–µ—Ä–æ—è—Ç–Ω—ã–µ —Ä–µ–∞–∫—Ü–∏–∏ –Ω–∞ —Ä–∞–∑–ª–∏—á–Ω—ã–µ –Ω–µ–±–ª–∞–≥–æ–ø—Ä–∏—è—Ç–Ω—ã–µ —Ñ–∏–Ω–∞–Ω—Å–æ–≤—ã–µ –∏–ª–∏ —Ç–µ—Ö–Ω–∏—á–µ—Å–∫–∏–µ —Å–æ–±—ã—Ç–∏—è.

The given code is a C++ code snippet that is part of the TON Blockchain Library. It includes classes and functions related to the Adnl (Abstract Datagram Network Layer) protocol implementation. Here is a detailed explanation of the code:

1. The code defines the AdnlInboundConnection class, which is responsible for processing incoming packets in the Adnl protocol. The process_packet function parses the incoming packet as an adnl_message_query, creates a response adnl_message_answer, and sends it back to the sender.

2. The process_init_packet function processes the initial packet received during the connection setup. It extracts the local ID from the packet, initializes the cryptographic settings, and resumes reading for further communication.

3. The inited_crypto function is a callback that is called after the cryptographic initialization is completed. It sends an empty buffer slice, resumes reading, and notifies the connection.

4. The process_custom_packet function handles custom packets based on their size and content. It can process tcp_ping, tcp_pong, tcp_authentificate, and tcp_authentificationComplete packets.

5. The AdnlExtServerImpl class manages the external Adnl server implementation. It includes functions to add TCP ports, handle accepted connections, and decrypt initial packets.

6. The add_tcp_port function adds a TCP port for listening to incoming connections. It creates a TcpInfiniteListener actor to accept incoming connections.

7. The add_local_id function adds a local ID to the server for decryption purposes.

8. The accepted function is called when a new connection is accepted. It creates a new AdnlInboundConnection actor to handle the incoming connection.

9. The decrypt_init_packet function decrypts the initial packet using the provided destination ID and forwards the decrypted data to the AdnlPeerTable for further processing.

10. The AdnlExtServerCreator class provides a static function create to create an instance of the AdnlExtServerImpl actor.

Flow of the code:
1. Incoming packets are processed by AdnlInboundConnection.
2. Initial packets are processed to initialize cryptographic settings.
3. Custom packets are handled based on their type and content.
4. The AdnlExtServerImpl manages external Adnl server implementation, including adding TCP ports and handling incoming connections.

G-BOTS mobile game launch

The G-BOTS game has officially launched, marking an important milestone for the owners of G-BOTS NFTs. They can now log into the game using their wallets to play with their NFT robots.

The game introduces a battle royale format where players compete in a PvP (player-versus-player) arena. The G-BOT NFT collection, notable for being the first 3D NFT collection on TON, comprises 6,666 unique NFT robots. Since its inception a year ago, the collection has reached a trading volume of approximately 192,000 Toncoin (TON) and is verified on Getgems.

Following this mobile game launch, the next step involves introducing the game on Telegram via a TON-based Mini App, further expanding the platform's reach to the messenger‚Äôs 800 million monthly active users.

The game is currently available on the Play Store for Android users and on the App Store for iOS devices.

‚ÄãThe Open League incentives start today

Today marks the beginning of The Open League incentives, with up to 1 million Toncoin (TON) set to be distributed to TON Community this month. Following the successful launch of Web3 quests aimed at introducing new users to various Web3 projects, liquidity pools for selected TON-based project tokens on DeDust and STON.fi will be boosted with Toncoin rewards.

The boost has already begun and will run until April 1, 2024. Projects that show the most traction in terms of Total Value Locked (TVL), highest utilization rates, daily active wallets, and transaction numbers will receive continuous boosts throughout March. The best projects will receive additional Toncoin awards on April 1, 2024, for their performance.

Meet the Open League contenders:

‚ñ™Ô∏è $STON - STON.fi
‚ñ™Ô∏è $SCALE - DeDust
‚ñ™Ô∏è $JNANO - Tonano
‚ñ™Ô∏è $PUNK - TON Punks
‚ñ™Ô∏è $FNZ - Fanzee
‚ñ™Ô∏è $MC - Tap Fantasy
‚ñ™Ô∏è $UP - TonUP
‚ñ™Ô∏è $RAFF - Ton Raffles
‚ñ™Ô∏è $ARBUZ - Arbuz
‚ñ™Ô∏è $GRAM - Gram
‚ñ™Ô∏è $JETTON - Jetton

How to participate:

‚ñ™Ô∏è DYOR: All selected projects have demonstrated growth and demand, qualifying them for reward distribution. However, liquidity pools carry inherent risks, and it's crucial to fully understand these before participating.
‚ñ™Ô∏è Provide liquidity: To join, you'll need tokens from both sides of the pool. Swap your Toncoin for your chosen project's token and deposit equal amounts into the pool.
‚ñ™Ô∏è Monitor your position: Reward amounts are subject to change, so monitoring the health of your position is vital. Be aware of impermanent loss, especially if the value of one side of your pool becomes highly volatile.
‚ñ™Ô∏è Earn: Rewards will be distributed automatically based on your pool share size. The larger your share, the greater your rewards.

Get started on DeDust or STON.fi.

Stay tuned to this channel for the latest updates, as reward distributions are subject to rapid changes. For more details. check out this blog post.

GOSH is Unveiling "DIE LAST", the Acki Nacki Validator Game. And It's Not What You Expect!

GOSH is thrilled to announce a unique validator game for the Acki Nacki network, launching exclusively on the Steam gaming platform. Brace yourselves for an epic 4X strategy adventure that runs entirely on the Acki Nacki network.

Set against a post-industrial backdrop, this survival, massively multiplayer 4x strategy game challenges you to regenerate the planet, harness renewable resources, and safeguard your economic interests and life.

Players have the opportunity to dive into two pivotal roles: become a Block Producer, managing your very own Acki Nacki hardware server, or step into the shoes of a Block Keeper, engaging in the thrilling day-to-day gameplay. By forming guilds, Block Producers and Keepers unite their strengths to secure and defend resources from rival guilds, making every decision count.

While the game is set to grace various distribution targets via the leading Steam Platform, it adheres to Steam's License terms by excluding in-game blockchain content. However, the door to Web3 content remains open through 3rd-party clients sparked by the creativity at the Acki Nacki "Underworld Computer" hackathon.

Get ready to mark your calendars and dive into a world where strategy and sustainability collide. The game's Steam page is just a click away: https://store.steampowered.com/app/2872100/DIE_LAST/?beta=1
For all the latest updates and release announcements, make sure to add it to your Steam Wishlists. Let's embark on this journey together!

–û–¥–Ω–∞–∫–æ —ç—Ñ—Ñ–µ–∫—Ç–∏–≤–Ω–æ—Å—Ç—å L2 —Ä–µ—à–µ–Ω–∏–π —Ç–µ—Å–Ω–æ —Å–≤—è–∑–∞–Ω–∞ —Å –∫–æ–ª–µ–±–∞–Ω–∏—è–º–∏ —Å—Ç–æ–∏–º–æ—Å—Ç–∏ –≥–∞–∑–∞ –Ω–∞ Ethereum. –ü–ª–∞—Ç–∞ –∑–∞ –≥–∞–∑ ‚Äî —Ü–µ–Ω–∞, –∫–æ—Ç–æ—Ä—É—é –ø–æ–ª—å–∑–æ–≤–∞—Ç–µ–ª–∏ –ø–ª–∞—Ç—è—Ç –∑–∞ –≤—ã–ø–æ–ª–Ω–µ–Ω–∏–µ —Ç—Ä–∞–Ω–∑–∞–∫—Ü–∏–π –∏ –∑–∞–ø—É—Å–∫ —Å–º–∞—Ä—Ç-–∫–æ–Ω—Ç—Ä–∞–∫—Ç–æ–≤ –Ω–∞ Ethereum ‚Äî –∫–æ–ª–µ–±–ª–µ—Ç—Å—è –≤ –∑–∞–≤–∏—Å–∏–º–æ—Å—Ç–∏ –æ—Ç –∞–∫—Ç–∏–≤–Ω–æ—Å—Ç–∏ —Å–µ—Ç–∏. –í—ã—Å–æ–∫–∏–π —Å–ø—Ä–æ—Å –Ω–∞ –≤—ã—á–∏—Å–ª–∏—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω—ã–µ —Ä–µ—Å—É—Ä—Å—ã Ethereum –ø–æ–≤—ã—à–∞–µ—Ç —Ü–µ–Ω—ã –Ω–∞ –≥–∞–∑, –≤ —Ç–æ –≤—Ä–µ–º—è –∫–∞–∫ –Ω–∏–∑–∫–∏–π —Å–ø—Ä–æ—Å –ø—Ä–∏–≤–æ–¥–∏—Ç –∫ —Å–Ω–∏–∂–µ–Ω–∏—é —Ü–µ–Ω –Ω–∞ –≥–∞–∑. –≠—Ç–∞ –ø–µ—Ä–µ–º–µ–Ω—á–∏–≤–æ—Å—Ç—å –≤–Ω–æ—Å–∏—Ç —Å–ª–æ–π —Ñ–∏–Ω–∞–Ω—Å–æ–≤–æ–π –Ω–µ–ø—Ä–µ–¥—Å–∫–∞–∑—É–µ–º–æ—Å—Ç–∏ –¥–ª—è –≤—Å–µ—Ö —É—á–∞—Å—Ç–Ω–∏–∫–æ–≤ —Å–µ—Ç–∏, –Ω–æ –æ—Å–æ–±–µ–Ω–Ω–æ –∑–∞—Ç—Ä–∞–≥–∏–≤–∞–µ—Ç —Å–µ—Ç–∏ L2. –•–æ—Ç—è L2 –ø—Ä–µ–¥–Ω–∞–∑–Ω–∞—á–µ–Ω—ã –¥–ª—è —Å–º—è–≥—á–µ–Ω–∏—è –Ω–µ–∫–æ—Ç–æ—Ä—ã—Ö –ø—Ä–æ–±–ª–µ–º —Å—Ç–æ–∏–º–æ—Å—Ç–∏, —Å–≤—è–∑–∞–Ω–Ω—ã—Ö —Å –≤—ã—Å–æ–∫–∏–º–∏ –ø–ª–∞—Ç–∞–º–∏ –∑–∞ –≥–∞–∑, –æ–±—Ä–∞–±–∞—Ç—ã–≤–∞—è —Ç—Ä–∞–Ω–∑–∞–∫—Ü–∏–∏ –±–æ–ª–µ–µ —ç—Ñ—Ñ–µ–∫—Ç–∏–≤–Ω–æ, –∏–º –≤—Å–µ —Ä–∞–≤–Ω–æ –Ω–µ–æ–±—Ö–æ–¥–∏–º–æ –≤–∑–∞–∏–º–æ–¥–µ–π—Å—Ç–≤–æ–≤–∞—Ç—å —Å –æ—Å–Ω–æ–≤–Ω–æ–π —Å–µ—Ç—å—é Ethereum –¥–ª—è –¥–æ—Å—Ç–∏–∂–µ–Ω–∏—è –æ–∫–æ–Ω—á–∞—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω–æ—Å—Ç–∏ —Ç—Ä–∞–Ω–∑–∞–∫—Ü–∏–∏. –≠—Ç–æ—Ç –ø–æ—Å–ª–µ–¥–Ω–∏–π —à–∞–≥ —Ç—Ä–µ–±—É–µ—Ç –æ–ø–ª–∞—Ç—ã –ø–ª–∞—Ç—ã –∑–∞ –≥–∞–∑ Ethereum, –¥–µ–ª–∞—è —Å–µ—Ç–∏ L2 –ø–æ–¥–≤–µ—Ä–∂–µ–Ω–Ω—ã–º–∏ —Ç–æ–π –∂–µ –≤–æ–ª–∞—Ç–∏–ª—å–Ω–æ—Å—Ç–∏, –∫–æ—Ç–æ—Ä–∞—è –∑–∞—Ç—Ä–∞–≥–∏–≤–∞–µ—Ç –≤—Å–µ—Ö –ø–æ–ª—å–∑–æ–≤–∞—Ç–µ–ª–µ–π Ethereum.

–ó–∞–≤–∏—Å–∏–º–æ—Å—Ç—å —Å–µ—Ç–µ–π L2 –æ—Ç Ethereum –¥–ª—è –æ–∫–æ–Ω—á–∞—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω–æ—Å—Ç–∏ —Ç—Ä–∞–Ω–∑–∞–∫—Ü–∏–π –æ–∑–Ω–∞—á–∞–µ—Ç, —á—Ç–æ –ª—é–±–æ–µ —É–≤–µ–ª–∏—á–µ–Ω–∏–µ —Ü–µ–Ω –Ω–∞ –≥–∞–∑ –Ω–∞–ø—Ä—è–º—É—é —É–≤–µ–ª–∏—á–∏–≤–∞–µ—Ç –æ–ø–µ—Ä–∞—Ü–∏–æ–Ω–Ω—ã–µ —Ä–∞—Å—Ö–æ–¥—ã, –ø–æ—Ç–µ–Ω—Ü–∏–∞–ª—å–Ω–æ —Ä–∞–∑–º—ã–≤–∞—è –ø—Ä–µ–∏–º—É—â–µ—Å—Ç–≤–∞ –≤ —Å—Ç–æ–∏–º–æ—Å—Ç–∏, –ø–æ–ª—É—á–µ–Ω–Ω—ã–µ –∑–∞ —Å—á–µ—Ç –æ–±—Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–∫–∏ —Ç—Ä–∞–Ω–∑–∞–∫—Ü–∏–π –≤–Ω–µ —Å–µ—Ç–∏. –î–ª—è L2 —Ä–µ—à–µ–Ω–∏–π, –∫–æ—Ç–æ—Ä—ã–µ –æ–±
